This paper deals with the computational complexity of computing rotation distance between trees, which is a problem in the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from parameterized complexity, which is a subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of computing rotation distance is closely related to problems in computational geometry, such as computing the edit distance between two planar graphs, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to the subcategories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
